{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sales of Apple products are increasing dramatically in new markets such as China. Apple platforms now support new localizations such as Arabic. Quality localization is critical to the success of your apps in these rapidly growing markets. This session will cover the things you need to know to succeed, including:1. What kind of language support is offered and how you can test. 2. Making your application localizable for these markets. 3. How to make sure your application supports bidirectional UI."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11-131-Getting-Your-Apps-Ready-for-China-and-other-Hot-New-Markets"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC11","title":"Getting Your Apps Ready for China and other Hot New Markets","role":"sampleCode"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc11-131-getting-your-apps-ready-for-china-and-other-hot-new-markets"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2011\/131\/","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex"}},"references":{"